                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 23700/16.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Hill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-04-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Adee informs Ambassador Hill that extradition of one Nicholas Knepper will
                    soon be granted by Luxemburg, and, as Belgian Government refuses transit of
                    prisoner except on full extradition formalities, he instructs him to ascertain
                    if the German Government will allow transit for agent and fugitive, and upon
                    what formalities. Says particulars relative to Knepper case may he obtained from
                    the legation at The Hague.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
